definition.value: A CMP-sugar having 3-deoxy-beta-D-manno-octulosonic acid as the sugar component.
A nitro fatty acid that is (9E)-octadec-9-enoic (elaidic) acid substituted by a nitro group at position 10.
Any nitrogen-containing fatty acid that is fatty acid containing at least one nitro group.
A GDP-hexose having 2,4-diacetamido-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose as the hexose component.
The cationic form of a C3 cyanine dye having 3-pentyl-1,3-benzoxazol-2(3H)-yl units at each end. A fluorescent compound that preferentially stains chronic myelogenic leukemia cells.
A pyrazolopyrimidine that is pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine bearing quinolin-4-yl and 4-isopropyloxyphenyl substituents at positions 3 and 6 respectively.

A member of the class of biindoles that is indirubin substituted at position 6 by a bromo group and in which the keto group at position 3' has undergone condensation with hydroxylamine to form the corresponding oxime.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dien-6-ynoic acid.
A fatty-acyl group derived from (9Z,12Z,15Z)-octadeca-9,12,15-trien-6-ynoic acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3,22-dioxochol-4-en-24-oic acid.
A ceramide in which the sphingoid component is specified as (4E,8E,10E)-sphinga-4,8,10-trienine
A fatty-acyl group derived from (9Z)-octadec-9-en-12-ynoic acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3beta-hydroxychola-5,20(22)-dien-24-oic acid.
A phenolate anion resulting from deprotonation of the phenolic hydroxy group of picric acid.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 5-hexenoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 5-hexynoyl.
A stilbenol that consists of trans-stilbene bearing a hydroxy group at position 4 as well as two methoxy substituents at positions 3' and 5'.
An organoammonium salt resulting from the formal reaction of butamben with 0.5 mol eq. of picric acid.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 20-methyl-3-oxopregna-4,17-dien-21-oic acid.
An ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the amino group of butamben.

A linear seventeen-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Phe-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by phenylalanyl [MBP83-99(F(91))].

A linear 27-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Phe-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by phenylalanyl [MBP83-99(F(91))] and with an (L-lysylglycyl)5 [(KG5)] linker attached to the glutamine(83) (E(83)) residue.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3beta-hydroxychol-5-en-24-oic acid.

A linear seventeen-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Tyr-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by tyrosyl [MBP83-99(Y(91))].

A linear 27-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Tyr-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by tyrosyl [MBP83-99(Y(91))] and with an (L-lysylglycyl)5 [(KG5)] linker attached to the glutamine(83) (E(83)) residue.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 17-hydroxy-3-oxopregn-4-en-20-carboxylic acid.

A linear seventeen-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-Ala-Phe-Phe-Lys-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the histidyl residue at position 88 replaced by alanyl [MBP83-99(A(88))].

A linear 27-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Glu-Asn-Pro-Val-Val-Ala-Phe-Phe-Lys-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the histidyl residue at position 88 replaced by alanyl [MBP83-99(A(88))] and with an (L-lysylglycyl)5 [(KG5)] linker attached to the glutamine(83) (E(83)) residue.

A linear seventeen-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Glu-Asn-Pro-Ala-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Lys-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the valyl residue at position 86 replaced by alanyl [MBP83-99(A(86))].

A linear 27-membered polypeptide comprising the sequence Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Lys-Gly-Glu-Asn-Pro-Ala-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Lys-Asn-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-Arg-Thr-Pro. Corresponds to the sequence of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the valyl residue at position 86 replaced by alanyl [MBP83-99(A(86))] and with an (L-lysylglycyl)5 [(KG5)] linker attached to the glutamine(83) (E(83)) residue.

A 17-membered homodetic cyclic peptide comprising the sequence -Arg-Thr-Pro-Glu-Asp-Pro-Val-Val-His-Phe-Phe-Phe-Asp-Ile-Val-Thr-Pro-. Cyclic analogue with head-to-tail cyclisation of the myelin basic protein 83-99 (MBP83-99) immunodominant epitope with the lysyl residue at position 91 replaced by phenylalanyl [MBP83-99(F(91))].
Any aliphatic sulfide in which at least one of the organyl groups attached to the sulfur is a methyl group.
A steroidal acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3beta-hydroxychola-5,22-dien-24-oic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group  of 2-methyl-3-oxopalmitic acid.
A hydrate that is the dihydrate form of copper(II) chloride. It occurs naturally as the mineral eriochalcite.
A hydroxycalciol that is vitamin D2 in which the hydrogen at position 25 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A hydroxycalciol that is vitamin D2 bearing additional hydroxy substituents at positions 1alpha and 25.
A 3-hydroxy-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxyoctanoic acid.
Any alkaloid that has significant antibiotic properties.

A compound that has a structure that is related to miconazole, contains an azole (imidazole or triazole) moiety, and has significant systemic antifungal properties.  They inhibit cytochrome P450-dependent enzymes (particularly C14-demethylase) involved in the biosynthesis of ergosterol, which is required for fungal cell membrane structure and function.
An organonitrogen heterocyclic antibiotic whose structure contains a quinolone or quinolone-related skeleton.

A member of the class of anthraquinone that is 1,4-diamino-9,10-anthraquinone in which the two amino groups are carrying 3-(diethylamino)-2-hydroxypropyl and (oxiran-2-yl)methyl substituents. It exhibits anti-cancer properties.
An N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl group derived from 6-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)]-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine.
Any antifungal agent used to prevent or treat fungal infections in humans or animals.
Any substance used in acriculture, horticulture, forestry, etc. for its fungicidal properties.
A nitro fatty acid that is (9E)-octadec-9-enoic (elaidic) acid substituted by a nitro group at position 9.
A hydroxyisoflavone that is  isoflavone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 7 and 4' and a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 8 via a C-glycosidic linkage.
